data.text:
A Descarga is the Cuban version of an improvised jam session. Son Montuno, Guajira, Bolero, Guaracha, Rumba y mas! Descarga is influenced by American Jazz. Descarga was born in Havana in the 1950’s. This week on LATIN EXPLOSION, I will feature Cachao, the biggest name in Descarga. Plus Chappottin, New York Boogaloo master Johnny Colon […]

Join Seany G as he plays the music of The Cars and Ric Ocasek on this week’s Second Wind.

Is Sarasota County Gerrymandering? Why redistrict County Commission districts now, when the 2020 census is just one year away? Are current county districts unfair, or is the County Commission wasting our money to serve their benefactors? Join Cathy Antunes with her guests Pat Rounds and Dan Lobeck while they discuss the latest updates on the […]

Not In My BackYard! Plans for apartments next to single family neighborhoods are making Sarasota residents nervous. Are they right? Are the new plans good for creating a walkable, affordable community, or do they fall short? Andrew Georgiadis is my guest this week when we discuss NIMBYs, Developers and good planning. Tune in Thursdays at […]

Suncoast Commission on the Status of Women (SCSW) will be commemorating the Centennial of Women’s Suffrage in 2020! SCSW President Gini Hyman is my guest this Thursday at 9 am. We’ll discuss plans to advance womens’ issues and voting in Sarasota County. Tune in Thursdays at 9 am to WSLR 96.5 fm (WBPV 100.1 fm […]

Join Whitehorse as he interviews Congresswoman Deb Haaland from New Mexico. On Nov. 6, 2018, Deb Haaland, from the Pueblo of Laguna tribe in New Mexico, became one of the first two Native American women to be elected to Congress.

Is County Redistricting really Local Gerrymandering in disguise? Pat Rounds is my guest! Tune in at 9 am for a discussion about our local constitution (or County Charter), Single Member Districts, and a historic look at the Sarasota County Commission’s efforts to limit or undo citizen input. Single Member districts’s in the House!

On The Detail: A recent face-off between Planning Commissioners and City Staff grabbed headlines. Some say the current Sarasota Planning Commission is one of the best we’ve every had! Join Cathy this morning when she interviews Planning Board Chair Eileen Normile about growth in Sarasota and how City processes are serving – or failing to […]

The Afro-Cuban Jazz Edition is a radio program in English that features the very best Latin Jazz from everywhere including new and recent Jazz recordings (sometimes with exclusive interviews and musical selections)The host Frankie Pineiro has done radio for the past 30 years, also a bandleader for Guisando Caliente Latin Jazz Quintet, Viva Cal Sextet, […]

New Show Alert! Mind.Your.Business. with Dana and Ryan is a 2-hour, bi-weekly, music-focused talk-show on Sarasota’s own Community Radio Station WSLR 96.5 LP-FM and WBPV 100.1 LP-FM in Bradenton.
